  "excerpt": "<p>If you had a Marketplace plan and used&nbsp;advance payments of the premium tax credit (APTC)&nbsp;to lower your monthly payment, you\u2019ll have to \u201creconcile\u201d when you file your federal taxes.</p>",
  "content": "<p>If you had a Marketplace plan and used the&nbsp;<a class=\"ck ck-tooltip\" href=\"/node/40036\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"688d3c9d-2e9b-4d91-a51b-fd13e51825e2\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"40036\" data-entity-bundle=\"brief\" title=\"Premium tax credit (term tooltip)\">premium tax credit</a>&nbsp;to lower your monthly payment, you\u2019ll have to \u201creconcile\u201d when you file your federal taxes. This means you\u2019ll compare:</p><ul><li>The amount of the premium tax credit you used during the year. (This was paid directly to your health plan so your monthly payment was lower.)</li><li>The premium tax credit you actually qualify for based on your final income for the year.</li></ul><p>Any difference between the two figures will affect your refund or tax owed.</p><div class=\"box-content information-lightweight\"><p>You should get your Form 1095-A in the mail by mid-February. It may be available in your Marketplace account anytime from mid-January to February 1. If you don't get it, or it's incorrect,&nbsp;<a href=\"/contact-us\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"2839b07e-0a5b-48bd-8fa4-ba9908d08200\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"39406\" data-entity-bundle=\"landing_page\" title=\"Contact us\">contact the Marketplace Call Center</a>.</p><p><a href=\"/tax-form-1095\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"6382f2ee-1765-433e-8f35-d21232410087\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"36146\" data-entity-bundle=\"article\" title=\"How to use Form 1095-A\">Get details on how to find your 1095-A form online</a><a data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"6382f2ee-1765-433e-8f35-d21232410087\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"36146\" data-entity-bundle=\"article\" href=\"/tax-form-1095\" title=\"How to use Form 1095-A\">.</a></p></div><h2>How to reconcile your premium tax credit</h2><ol><li>Get your Form 1095-A.</li><li>Print <a href=\"https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/f8962.pdf\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"7fc4e15a-edd5-43aa-891d-01e8feb938c5\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"40476\" data-entity-bundle=\"link\" title=\"IRS Form 8962 - 2025\">Form 8962, Premium Tax Credit</a>&nbsp;(PDF, 115 KB) and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/i8962.pdf\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"bc1e2342-db2a-459a-adca-21033ec9f3f0\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"40481\" data-entity-bundle=\"link\" title=\"IRS Form 8962 Instructions - 2025\">Form 8962 instructions</a>&nbsp;(PDF, 393 KB).</li><li>Use the information from your 1095-A form to complete Part II of Form 8962.</li></ol><div style=\"margin-left:30px;\"><p>Select the information you need to get details:</p><dl class=\"accordion learn-accordion\"><dt class=\"accordion-title\">Enrollment Premiums</dt><dd class=\"accordion-content\"><p><strong>Where to find it on Form 1095-A:</strong>&nbsp;Part III: Column A</p><ul><li>Annual amount: Line 33</li><li>Monthly amounts: Lines 21 -&nbsp;32</li></ul><p><strong>Where to enter it on Form 8962:</strong>&nbsp;Part II: Column a</p><ul><li>Annual amount: Line 11</li><li>Monthly amounts: Lines 12 -&nbsp;23</li></ul><p><strong>How to move enrollment premium info to Form 8962</strong></p><article class=\"media media--type-image media--view-mode-default\" data-align=\"center\">\n  \n      \n  <div class=\"field field--name-field-media-image field--type-image field--label-visually_hidden\">\n    <div class=\"field__label visually-hidden\">Image</div>\n              <div class=\"field__item\">    <img loading=\"eager\" data-image-encoded=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-image-width=\"1716\" data-image-height=\"1080\" srcset=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_small_544/public/inline-images/en/reconcile-premiums.png?itok=PSaxcYQl 544w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_medium_768/public/inline-images/en/reconcile-premiums.png?itok=7b_twP7S 768w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/en/reconcile-premiums.png?itok=SzI0-Swb 1024w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1290px) 1290px, 100vw\" width=\"1024\" height=\"644\" src=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/en/reconcile-premiums.png?itok=SzI0-Swb\" alt=\"Fields on Form 1095-A pointing to corresponding fields on Form 8962 for annual premium and monthly premium amounts. Had the same plan and premium all 12 months? Just copy your annual total to Form 8962. Had different plans or premiums during different months? Copy each monthly figure to Form 8962.\" title=\"Fields on Form 1095-A pointing to corresponding fields on Form 8962 for annual premium and monthly premium amounts. Had the same plan and premium all 12 months? Just copy your annual total to Form 8962. Had different plans or premiums during different months? Copy each monthly figure to Form 8962.\">\n\n\n</div>\n          </div>\n\n            <div class=\"field field--name-field-spanish-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item\"><article class=\"media media--type-image-es media--view-mode-default\">\n  \n      \n            <div class=\"field field--name-field-media-image-spanish field--type-image field--label-hidden field__item\">    <img loading=\"eager\" data-image-encoded=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-image-width=\"1716\" data-image-height=\"1080\" srcset=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_small_544/public/inline-images/es/reconcile-premiums.png?itok=Y9EJkVDz 544w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_medium_768/public/inline-images/es/reconcile-premiums.png?itok=jDfaoGBL 768w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/es/reconcile-premiums.png?itok=3Qv26s8L 1024w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1290px) 1290px, 100vw\" width=\"1024\" height=\"644\" src=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/es/reconcile-premiums.png?itok=3Qv26s8L\" alt>\n\n\n</div>\n      \n  </article>\n</div>\n      \n  </article>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></dd></dl><dl class=\"accordion learn-accordion\"><dt class=\"accordion-title\">Second lowest cost Silver plan (SLCSP) premium</dt><dd class=\"accordion-content\"><p><strong>Where to find it on Form 1095-A:</strong>&nbsp;Part III: Column B</p><ul><li>Annual amount: Line 33</li><li>Monthly amounts: Lines 21-32</li></ul><p><a href=\"/tax-tool/#/\">Use our tax tool to confirm the second lowest cost Silver plan amount.</a></p><p><strong>Where to enter it on Form 8962:</strong> Part II: Column b</p><ul><li>Annual amount: Line 11</li><li>Monthly amounts: Lines 21-23</li></ul><p><strong>How to move second lowest cost Silver plan (SLCSP) premium info to Form 8962</strong></p><article class=\"media media--type-image media--view-mode-default\" data-align=\"center\">\n  \n      \n  <div class=\"field field--name-field-media-image field--type-image field--label-visually_hidden\">\n    <div class=\"field__label visually-hidden\">Image</div>\n              <div class=\"field__item\">    <img loading=\"eager\" data-image-encoded=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-image-width=\"1716\" data-image-height=\"1080\" srcset=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_small_544/public/inline-images/en/reconcile-silver.png?itok=aWCqlCSp 544w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_medium_768/public/inline-images/en/reconcile-silver.png?itok=OhbJ1Fy3 768w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/en/reconcile-silver.png?itok=QCrDkMrI 1024w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1290px) 1290px, 100vw\" width=\"1024\" height=\"644\" src=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/en/reconcile-silver.png?itok=QCrDkMrI\" alt=\"Fields on Form 1095-A pointing to corresponding fields on Form 8962 for second lowest cost Silver plan premium. Had the same plan and premium all 12 months? Just copy your annual total to Form 8962. Had different plans or premiums during different months? Copy each monthly figure to Form 8962.\" title=\"Fields on Form 1095-A pointing to corresponding fields on Form 8962 for second lowest cost Silver plan premium. Had the same plan and premium all 12 months? Just copy your annual total to Form 8962. Had different plans or premiums during different months? Copy each monthly figure to Form 8962.\">\n\n\n</div>\n          </div>\n\n            <div class=\"field field--name-field-spanish-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item\"><article class=\"media media--type-image-es media--view-mode-default\">\n  \n      \n            <div class=\"field field--name-field-media-image-spanish field--type-image field--label-hidden field__item\">    <img loading=\"eager\" data-image-encoded=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-image-width=\"1716\" data-image-height=\"1080\" srcset=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_small_544/public/inline-images/es/reconcile-silver.png?itok=w8mVkJeN 544w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_medium_768/public/inline-images/es/reconcile-silver.png?itok=T6tDZeQT 768w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/es/reconcile-silver.png?itok=534DTG-e 1024w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1290px) 1290px, 100vw\" width=\"1024\" height=\"644\" src=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/es/reconcile-silver.png?itok=534DTG-e\" alt>\n\n\n</div>\n      \n  </article>\n</div>\n      \n  </article>\n</dd></dl><dl class=\"accordion learn-accordion\"><dt class=\"accordion-title\">Advance payment of premium tax credit</dt><dd class=\"accordion-content\"><p><strong>Where to find it on Form 1095-A:</strong> Part III: Column C</p><ul><li>Annual amount: Line 33</li><li>Monthly amounts: Lines 21-32</li></ul><p><strong>Where to enter it on Form 8962:</strong> Part II: Column f</p><ul><li>Annual amount: Line 11</li><li>Monthly amounts: Lines 21-23</li></ul><p><strong>How to move advance payment of premium tax credit info to Form 8962</strong></p><article class=\"media media--type-image media--view-mode-default\" data-align=\"center\">\n  \n      \n  <div class=\"field field--name-field-media-image field--type-image field--label-visually_hidden\">\n    <div class=\"field__label visually-hidden\">Image</div>\n              <div class=\"field__item\">    <img loading=\"eager\" data-image-encoded=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-image-width=\"1716\" data-image-height=\"1080\" srcset=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_small_544/public/inline-images/en/reconcile-credit.png?itok=yH45W0QA 544w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_medium_768/public/inline-images/en/reconcile-credit.png?itok=_YH5UeIz 768w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/en/reconcile-credit.png?itok=wXed_vC2 1024w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1290px) 1290px, 100vw\" width=\"1024\" height=\"644\" src=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/en/reconcile-credit.png?itok=wXed_vC2\" alt=\"Fields on Form 1095-A pointing to corresponding fields on Form 8962 for advance payment of premium tax credit. Had the same plan and premium all 12 months? Just copy your annual total to Form 8962. Had different plans or premiums during different months? Copy each monthly figure to Form 8962.\" title=\"Fields on Form 1095-A pointing to corresponding fields on Form 8962 for advance payment of premium tax credit. Had the same plan and premium all 12 months? Just copy your annual total to Form 8962. Had different plans or premiums during different months? Copy each monthly figure to Form 8962.\">\n\n\n</div>\n          </div>\n\n            <div class=\"field field--name-field-spanish-image field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item\"><article class=\"media media--type-image-es media--view-mode-default\">\n  \n      \n            <div class=\"field field--name-field-media-image-spanish field--type-image field--label-hidden field__item\">    <img loading=\"eager\" data-image-encoded=\"data:image/png;base64,\" data-image-width=\"1716\" data-image-height=\"1080\" srcset=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_small_544/public/inline-images/es/reconcile-credit.png?itok=LwG30W4n 544w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_medium_768/public/inline-images/es/reconcile-credit.png?itok=OfzfSUaj 768w, /sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/es/reconcile-credit.png?itok=EXISjR-B 1024w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1290px) 1290px, 100vw\" width=\"1024\" height=\"644\" src=\"/sites/default/files/styles/gatsby_large_1024/public/inline-images/es/reconcile-credit.png?itok=EXISjR-B\" alt>\n\n\n</div>\n      \n  </article>\n</div>\n      \n  </article>\n</dd></dl></div><ol start=\"4\"><li><span>Complete all sections of Form 8962. On Line 26, you\u2019ll find out if you used more or less premium tax credit than you qualify for based on your final 2025 income. This will affect the amount of your refund or tax due.</span></li><li><span>Include your completed Form 8962 with your 2025&nbsp;federal tax return.</span></li></ol><h2>What happens if you don\u2019t reconcile your taxes</h2><p>If you had a <span>2025</span> Marketplace plan but didn\u2019t file and&nbsp;reconcile&nbsp;your <strong>2024</strong> taxes, you may lose any savings you\u2019re getting for your 2026 plan.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>You\u2019ll get a letter from the Marketplace with details about what you need to do.</li><li>You may also get \u201c<a href=\"https://www.irs.gov/individuals/understanding-your-letter-12c\" data-entity-bundle data-entity-id data-internal-href target>Letter 12C</a>\u201d from the IRS.</li></ul><p>If you haven\u2019t filed your 2025 tax return \u2014 or filed a return but didn\u2019t reconcile the premium tax credit for all household members \u2014 you must do so immediately.</p><p>If you confirm that you filed your 2024 tax return, you won\u2019t need to do anything else.</p><h3>More on 2024 taxes&nbsp;</h3><ul><li><a href=\"/taxes-2024/how-coverage-affects-taxes\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"b33efc77-6f55-4e10-b324-31969274517a\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"40431\" data-entity-bundle=\"article\" title=\"How health coverage affects your 2024 federal income tax return\">Get more tax filing information.</a></li><li><a href=\"/taxes\" data-entity-type=\"node\" data-entity-uuid=\"706de1c9-a5eb-4066-a3b5-696e23078d56\" data-entity-substitution=\"canonical\" data-entity-id=\"36161\" data-entity-bundle=\"article\" title=\" 2025 health coverage &amp; your federal taxes\">Learn more about your health coverage and federal taxes.</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.irs.gov/help/ita\">Confirm your tax filing status for 2024&nbsp;using the Interactive Tax Assistant from the IRS.</a></li></ul>",
